ProMED
e-mail: promed@promedmail.org
[Trichinellosis is a parasitic disease of public health importance caused
by the nematode (worm) _Trichinella spiralis_. Human infections are
established by consumption of inadequately cooked infected meat, usually
pork or bear, although other species have been implicated. Natural
infections occur in wild carnivores; trichinellosis has been found in
horses, rats, beavers, opossums, walruses, whales and meat-eating birds.
Most mammals are susceptible. - Mod.TG
